IRS990.Desc: Historic Train Operation The Museum's mission is the collection preservation restortation and operation of vintage railroad equipment at its own facility and on the historic SD&A Railway for the education of current and future generations. This includes maintaining a research library for railroad transportation.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Public is welcome to become members of the museum after paying a yearly set of dues.
Anyone has been a dues paying member for one year or more and whose dues are current are entitled to vote in the election for the board of directors which is the governing body of the organization.

Changes to the organization bylaws and the sale of certain pieces of the museum's assets and historical collection require a vote of all members who have paid their yearly dues and are in good standing.

The Museum's accounting records and preparation of 990 and other financial documents are maintained and prepared by the treasurer. Upon completion of the return a draft was sent via email to all current board members for their review and approval. Upon approval by the board the final copy was presented to the president of the organization for signature and filing.
Requests are accepted by telephone email or postal mail.
